# Component Organization

- Never create new component files directly under `app/components/` without context.
- Every new component must live inside a feature/domain folder (e.g. `app/components/opportunities/`, `app/components/listing/`, `app/components/layout/`).
- If no suitable folder exists, create a new contextual folder first, then add the component inside it.
- Keep shared primitives only in `app/components/ui/`.
- Keep provider components only in `app/components/providers/`.

## Examples

- Bad: `app/components/interest-level-star-picker.tsx` (solto na raiz de `components/`)
- Good: `app/components/shared/interest-level-star-picker.tsx` (compartilhado entre domínios)
- Good: `app/components/opportunities/...` (específico de oportunidades)

## Refactor Preference

- When touching existing code, prefer moving/colocating orphan components into contextual folders instead of adding more files at the root of `app/components/`.
